{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/colic-infantile/diagnosis/differential-diagnosis/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"4fce8a03-6ca2-5480-9219-7b2a8e30f602","slug":"differential-diagnosis","fullItemName":"Differential diagnosis","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 87d0be65-95c2-4f35-a7ea-a880aea09429 --><h2>What is the differential diagnosis of infantile colic?</h2><!-- end field 87d0be65-95c2-4f35-a7ea-a880aea09429 -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 8c2ac170-2d4e-4baa-bcb9-0faa3f7042e1 --><!-- begin field f403f4de-b092-474f-bd6d-464b4a4d3a69 --><p><strong>Be aware that signs of organic disease in infants can be non-specific. Other possible causes of excessive, inconsolable crying include:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>If symptoms started suddenly and recently:</strong><ul><li>Intussusception or volvulus — suggested by bile-stained (green or yellow-green vomit), blood in the stool, and abdominal distension, tenderness, or a palpable mass.</li><li>Pyloric stenosis — suggested by frequent, forceful (projectile) vomiting in infants up to 2 months of age.</li><li>Incarcerated/strangulated hernia or torsion of the testis. See the CKS topic on <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/scrotal-pain-swelling/\">Scrotal pain and swelling</a> for more information.</li><li>Infection or sepsis. See the CKS topics on <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/meningitis-bacterial-meningitis-meningococcal-disease/\">Meningitis - bacterial meningitis and meningococcal disease</a>, <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/urinary-tract-infection-children/\">Urinary tract infection - children</a>, <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/otitis-media-acute/\">Otitis media - acute</a>, and <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/neutropenic-sepsis/\">Neutropenic sepsis</a> for more information.</li><li>Corneal abrasion (such as from a scratch from the infant's nails). See the CKS topic on <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/corneal-superficial-injury/\">Corneal superficial injury</a> for more information.</li><li>Accidental trauma or child maltreatment. See the CKS topic on <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/child-maltreatment-recognition-management/\">Child maltreatment - recognition and management</a> for more information.</li></ul></li><li><strong>If symptoms are more persistent:</strong><ul><li>Discomfort.<ul><li>Hunger or dehydration.</li><li>Excessive heat or cold.</li><li>Skin rash or itch (for example caused by eczema, or itchy clothes or clothes labels), or nappy rash. See the CKS topics on <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/eczema-atopic/\">Eczema - atopic</a> and <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/nappy-rash/\">Nappy rash</a> for more information.</li><li>Wind (may be due to inadequate winding technique).</li><li>Constipation. See the CKS topic on <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/constipation-in-children/\">Constipation in children</a> for more information.</li><li>Gastro-oesophageal reflux disease (GORD). See the CKS topic on <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/gord-in-children/\">GORD in children</a> for more information.</li></ul></li><li>Cows' milk protein allergy (CMPA) or transient lactose intolerance (rare). See the CKS topic on <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/\">Cows&#39; milk protein allergy in children</a> for more information.</li><li>Seizures, infantile spasms (rare). See the CKS topic on <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/epilepsy/\">Epilepsy</a> for more information.</li><li>Congenital or metabolic disorders, chromosomal abnormalities (rare).</li></ul></li></ul><!-- end field f403f4de-b092-474f-bd6d-464b4a4d3a69 --><!-- end item 8c2ac170-2d4e-4baa-bcb9-0faa3f7042e1 -->","topic":{"id":"e728c26a-005e-5e2a-9f46-f7dfec2cd36d","topicId":"254c369e-40fc-4169-bb92-30394399e7a4","topicName":"Colic - infantile","slug":"colic-infantile","lastRevised":"Last revised in June 2017","chapters":[{"id":"7a1f51d7-41cf-55a8-b71c-4d46909d5b0d","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"9d366893-0b5e-5935-a891-e27308683472","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"92f7cd8e-be30-5c7a-9859-062f74d2fd76","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"29f83c05-485a-5dfe-9c41-548aa53dac7e","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"74255d9b-c133-5715-b340-d8bcf73ede99","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"b8fa0a59-acfb-55c8-9dcd-622a14e70f4e","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"85fb7ab5-907c-53bb-9341-53b717308830","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"3f55b4fd-1c0a-517f-8936-e05ef8f1c1f4","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"2684a3a6-6535-5c17-9352-e8dfae930813","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"8fc37b28-2832-51b0-8068-54d4b3ba6bf1","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"d9fff9d3-37f5-5235-a336-f9a5c34ad1f5","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":"QIPP - Options for local implementation"},{"id":"464b9f75-1b8f-55fe-883e-0c2cee1438f9","slug":"nice-quality-standards","fullItemName":"NICE quality standards"}]},{"id":"3f35ca43-b738-5669-a5e1-7b965e35c7ff","fullItemName":"Background information","slug":"background-information","subChapters":[{"id":"e56f6e18-7e9b-502b-aa32-a45635f54cb0","slug":"definition","fullItemName":"Definition"},{"id":"8cfc6ae8-74a7-546a-b319-c166dac66e7b","slug":"causes","fullItemName":"Causes"},{"id":"b6f04831-ef5b-5776-9266-b152d2abf880","slug":"prevalence","fullItemName":"Prevalence"},{"id":"d60931fb-834f-5a78-8b0b-3a0dbc82b70f","slug":"complications","fullItemName":"Complications"},{"id":"c5658f48-8eb7-591a-bacd-368e8d453b21","slug":"prognosis","fullItemName":"Prognosis"}]},{"id":"05189512-66da-5bbd-b06e-214512dcf991","fullItemName":"Diagnosis","slug":"diagnosis","subChapters":[{"id":"42bd1a60-6292-5915-a979-8aa1f8291c76","slug":"assessment","fullItemName":"Assessment"},{"id":"4fce8a03-6ca2-5480-9219-7b2a8e30f602","slug":"differential-diagnosis","fullItemName":"Differential diagnosis"}]},{"id":"c78ea3ae-af06-5791-824f-415ef3269099","fullItemName":"Management","slug":"management","subChapters":[{"id":"3523ca84-e86f-51f1-8397-47660bbc2fe2","slug":"management","fullItemName":"Scenario: Management"}]},{"id":"d3874750-7638-5c06-94de-dae80dda043e","fullItemName":"Supporting evidence","slug":"supporting-evidence","subChapters":[]},{"id":"8f9b8813-14b8-51a5-990c-7bd6c1418656","fullItemName":"How this topic was developed","slug":"how-this-topic-was-developed","subChapters":[{"id":"84b25a5d-f179-549f-9006-ff00f546ad1d","slug":"search-strategy","fullItemName":"Search strategy"},{"id":"6c67fddc-0730-5503-8320-52fda75c9ac9","slug":"stakeholder-engagement","fullItemName":"Stakeholder engagement"},{"id":"4edfe879-cb84-5ea1-abb1-b40837e2f67e","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria"},{"id":"b6b34c02-df1a-5c7b-968d-706b2b7c6ec3","slug":"organizational-behavioural-financial-barriers","fullItemName":"Organizational, behavioural and financial barriers"},{"id":"929ed617-46fe-5ca1-821b-9d052bd4adf0","slug":"declarations-of-interest","fullItemName":"Declarations of interest"}]},{"id":"cbf4141b-6af2-5d1a-9deb-d847b9cd30c7","fullItemName":"References","slug":"references","subChapters":[]}]},"parentChapter":{"id":"05189512-66da-5bbd-b06e-214512dcf991","slug":"diagnosis","fullItemName":"Diagnosis"},"subChapters":[{"id":"53dae24b-408a-58d4-9abd-c5cd57d21221","slug":"basis-for-recommendation-2e9","fullItemName":"Basis for recommendation","depth":3,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 8210d3f1-aa15-4ea9-8029-bc57ff14799d --><h3>Basis for recommendation</h3><!-- end field 8210d3f1-aa15-4ea9-8029-bc57ff14799d -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 2e98f3b4-c176-4ee0-8e53-418bfed2fe0c --><!-- begin field 238b425d-ac4a-4551-9ee5-2ff2fc24e900 --><p>The information on differential diagnosis is based on the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) clinical guideline <em>Postnatal care: Routine postnatal care of women and their babies </em>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/colic-infantile/references/\">NICE, 2015</a>], the NICE clinical guideline <em>Food allergy in children and young people: Diagnosis and assessment of food allergy in children and young people in primary care and community settings </em>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/colic-infantile/references/\">NICE, 2011</a>], the Australian regional guideline <em>Infants and children: acute management of the unsettled and crying infant</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/colic-infantile/references/\">NSW Ministry of Health, 2016</a>], and expert opinion in review articles on infantile colic [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/colic-infantile/references/\">DTB, 2013</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/colic-infantile/references/\">Johnson, 2015</a>] and unexplained crying in infants [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/colic-infantile/references/\">Allister, 2014</a>].</p><!-- end field 238b425d-ac4a-4551-9ee5-2ff2fc24e900 --><!-- end item 2e98f3b4-c176-4ee0-8e53-418bfed2fe0c -->","subChapters":[]}]}}},"staticQueryHashes":["3666801979"]}